title: Putin and Xi praise 'no limits friendship' during Chinese president's trip to Russia
description: Vladimir Putin has welcomed his Chinese counterpart Xi Jinping to Moscow, just days after a warrant was issued for the Russian president's arrest over alleged war crimes in Ukraine.

title: French government faces motions of no confidence over pension reforms
description: France President Emmanuel Macron's government faces two motions of no confidence after attempting to push through plans to raise the country's pension age.

title: 'No one else wants to be friends with us': View from the China-Russia border city where harmony lies
description: If you want to understand the China-Russia relationship, the frozen border city of Heihe is a good place to start.

title: COVID 'did not affect' happiness levels around the world
description: People around the world did not report being more unhappy during the COVID pandemic than in the years before it, according to a study.

title: Punjab state on high alert as separatist preacher remains on the run
description: The state of Punjab in India remains on high alert as police continue their hunt for Amritpal Singh, a separatist leader who supports the Khalistan movement for a separate Sikh homeland.

title: North Korea simulates nuclear counterattack against US and South Korea
description: North Korea says it has simulated a nuclear counterattack against the US and South Korea as it fired another ballistic missile over the weekend - its fifth this month.

title: Taliban leader tells officials to 'sack your sons' in decree against nepotism

title: Former Australian soldier charged for alleged Afghanistan war crime
description: An Australian veteran has been charged for the alleged murder of an Afghan man, following an investigation into war crimes.

title: Removing millions of dead fish from Australian river will be 'logistical nightmare'
description: Removing millions of rotting fish from a river in the Australian outback will be a "logistical nightmare", according to police.

title: Donald Trump says he's going to be arrested this week - so what could happen if he is?
description: Donald Trump has claimed he will be arrested this week over an alleged hush money payment to adult film star Stormy Daniels.
